19template <class Next>
20class MaglevEarlyLoweringReducer : public Next {
21 // This Reducer provides some helpers that are used during
22 // MaglevGraphBuildingPhase to lower some Maglev operators. Depending on what
23 // we decide going forward (regarding SimplifiedLowering for instance), we
24 // could introduce new Simplified or JS operations instead of using these
25 // helpers to lower, and turn the helpers into regular REDUCE methods in the
26 // new simplified lowering or in MachineLoweringReducer.
27
28 public:
29 TURBOSHAFT_REDUCER_BOILERPLATE(MaglevEarlyLowering)
30
31 void CheckInstanceType(V<Object> input, V<FrameState> frame_state,
32 const FeedbackSource& feedback,
33 InstanceType first_instance_type,
34 InstanceType last_instance_type, bool check_smi) {
35 if (check_smi) {
36 __ DeoptimizeIf(__ IsSmi(input), frame_state,
37 DeoptimizeReason::kWrongInstanceType, feedback);
38 }
39
40 V<i::Map> map = __ LoadMapField(input);
41
42 if (first_instance_type == last_instance_type) {
43#if V8_STATIC_ROOTS_BOOL
44 if (InstanceTypeChecker::UniqueMapOfInstanceType(first_instance_type)) {
45 base::Optional<RootIndex> expected_index =
46 InstanceTypeChecker::UniqueMapOfInstanceType(first_instance_type);
47 CHECK(expected_index.has_value());
48 Handle<HeapObject> expected_map = Handle<HeapObject>::cast(
49 isolate_->root_handle(expected_index.value()));
50 __ DeoptimizeIfNot(__ TaggedEqual(map, __ HeapConstant(expected_map)),
51 frame_state, DeoptimizeReason::kWrongInstanceType,
52 feedback);
53 return;
54 }
55#endif // V8_STATIC_ROOTS_BOOL
56 V<Word32> instance_type = __ LoadInstanceTypeField(map);
57 __ DeoptimizeIfNot(__ Word32Equal(instance_type, first_instance_type),
58 frame_state, DeoptimizeReason::kWrongInstanceType,
59 feedback);
60 } else {
61 __ DeoptimizeIfNot(CompareInstanceTypeRange(map, first_instance_type,
62 last_instance_type),
63 frame_state, DeoptimizeReason::kWrongInstanceType,
64 feedback);
65 }
66 }
67
68 V<InternalizedString> CheckedInternalizedString(
69 V<Object> object, OpIndex frame_state, bool check_smi,
70 const FeedbackSource& feedback) {
71 if (check_smi) {
72 __ DeoptimizeIf(__ IsSmi(object), frame_state, DeoptimizeReason::kSmi,
73 feedback);
74 }
75
76 Label<InternalizedString> done(this);
77 V<Map> map = __ LoadMapField(object);
78 V<Word32> instance_type = __ LoadInstanceTypeField(map);
79
80 // Go to the slow path if this is a non-string, or a non-internalised
81 // string.
82 static_assert((kStringTag | kInternalizedTag) == 0);
83 IF (UNLIKELY(__ Word32BitwiseAnd(
84 instance_type, kIsNotStringMask | kIsNotInternalizedMask))) {
85 // Deopt if this isn't a string.
86 __ DeoptimizeIf(__ Word32BitwiseAnd(instance_type, kIsNotStringMask),
87 frame_state, DeoptimizeReason::kWrongMap, feedback);
88 // Deopt if this isn't a thin string.
89 static_assert(base::bits::CountPopulation(kThinStringTagBit) == 1);
90 __ DeoptimizeIfNot(__ Word32BitwiseAnd(instance_type, kThinStringTagBit),
91 frame_state, DeoptimizeReason::kWrongMap, feedback);
92 // Load internalized string from thin string.
93 V<InternalizedString> intern_string =
94 __ template LoadField<InternalizedString>(
95 object, AccessBuilder::ForThinStringActual());
96 GOTO(done, intern_string);
97 } ELSE {
98 GOTO(done, V<InternalizedString>::Cast(object));
99 }
100
101 BIND(done, result);
102 return result;
103 }
104
105 void CheckValueEqualsString(V<Object> object, InternalizedStringRef value,
106 V<FrameState> frame_state,
107 const FeedbackSource& feedback) {
108 IF_NOT (LIKELY(__ TaggedEqual(object, __ HeapConstant(value.object())))) {
109 __ DeoptimizeIfNot(__ ObjectIsString(object), frame_state,
110 DeoptimizeReason::kNotAString, feedback);
111 V<Boolean> is_same_string_bool =
112 __ StringEqual(V<String>::Cast(object),
113 __ template HeapConstant<String>(value.object()));
114 __ DeoptimizeIf(
115 __ RootEqual(is_same_string_bool, RootIndex::kFalseValue, isolate_),
116 frame_state, DeoptimizeReason::kWrongValue, feedback);
117 }
118 }
119
120 V<Object> CheckConstructResult(V<Object> construct_result,
121 V<Object> implicit_receiver) {
122 // If the result is an object (in the ECMA sense), we should get rid
123 // of the receiver and use the result; see ECMA-262 version 5.1
124 // section 13.2.2-7 on page 74.
125 Label<Object> done(this);
126
127 GOTO_IF(
128 __ RootEqual(construct_result, RootIndex::kUndefinedValue, isolate_),
129 done, implicit_receiver);
130
131 // If the result is a smi, it is *not* an object in the ECMA sense.
132 GOTO_IF(__ IsSmi(construct_result), done, implicit_receiver);
133
134 // Check if the type of the result is not an object in the ECMA sense.
135 GOTO_IF(JSAnyIsNotPrimitive(construct_result), done, construct_result);
136
137 // Throw away the result of the constructor invocation and use the
138 // implicit receiver as the result.
139 GOTO(done, implicit_receiver);
140
141 BIND(done, result);
142 return result;
143 }
144
145 void CheckConstTrackingLetCellTagged(V<Context> context, V<Object> value,
146 int index, V<FrameState> frame_state,
147 const FeedbackSource& feedback) {
148 V<Object> old_value =
149 __ LoadTaggedField(context, Context::OffsetOfElementAt(index));
150 IF_NOT (__ TaggedEqual(old_value, value)) {
151 CheckConstTrackingLetCell(context, index, frame_state, feedback);
152 }
153 }
154
155 void CheckConstTrackingLetCell(V<Context> context, int index,
156 V<FrameState> frame_state,
157 const FeedbackSource& feedback) {
158 // Load the const tracking let side data.
159 V<Object> side_data = __ LoadTaggedField(
160 context, Context::OffsetOfElementAt(
161 Context::CONST_TRACKING_LET_SIDE_DATA_INDEX));
162 V<Object> index_data = __ LoadTaggedField(
163 side_data, FixedArray::OffsetOfElementAt(
164 index - Context::MIN_CONTEXT_EXTENDED_SLOTS));
165 // If the field is already marked as "not a constant", storing a
166 // different value is fine. But if it's anything else (including the hole,
167 // which means no value was stored yet), deopt this code. The lower tier
168 // code will update the side data and invalidate DependentCode if needed.
169 V<Word32> is_const = __ TaggedEqual(
170 index_data, __ SmiConstant(ConstTrackingLetCell::kNonConstMarker));
171 __ DeoptimizeIfNot(is_const, frame_state,
172 DeoptimizeReason::kConstTrackingLet, feedback);
173 }
174
175 V<Smi> UpdateJSArrayLength(V<Word32> length_raw, V<JSArray> object,
176 V<Word32> index) {
177 Label<Smi> done(this);
178 IF (__ Uint32LessThan(index, length_raw)) {
179 GOTO(done, __ TagSmi(length_raw));
180 } ELSE {
181 V<Word32> new_length_raw =
182 __ Word32Add(index, 1); // This cannot overflow.
183 V<Smi> new_length_tagged = __ TagSmi(new_length_raw);
184 __ Store(object, new_length_tagged, StoreOp::Kind::TaggedBase(),
185 MemoryRepresentation::TaggedSigned(),
186 WriteBarrierKind::kNoWriteBarrier, JSArray::kLengthOffset);
187 GOTO(done, new_length_tagged);
188 }
189
190 BIND(done, length_tagged);
191 return length_tagged;
192 }
193
194 private:
195 V<Word32> JSAnyIsNotPrimitive(V<Object> heap_object) {
196 V<Map> map = __ LoadMapField(heap_object);
197 if (V8_STATIC_ROOTS_BOOL) {
198 // All primitive object's maps are allocated at the start of the read only
199 // heap. Thus JS_RECEIVER's must have maps with larger (compressed)
200 // addresses.
201 return __ Uint32LessThanOrEqual(
202 InstanceTypeChecker::kNonJsReceiverMapLimit,
203 __ TruncateWordPtrToWord32(__ BitcastTaggedToWordPtr(map)));
204 } else {
205 static_assert(LAST_JS_RECEIVER_TYPE == LAST_TYPE);
206 return __ Uint32LessThanOrEqual(FIRST_JS_RECEIVER_TYPE,
207 __ LoadInstanceTypeField(map));
208 }
209 }
210
211 V<Word32> CompareInstanceTypeRange(V<Map> map,
212 InstanceType first_instance_type,
213 InstanceType last_instance_type) {
214 V<Word32> instance_type = __ LoadInstanceTypeField(map);
215
216 if (first_instance_type == 0) {
217 return __ Uint32LessThanOrEqual(instance_type, last_instance_type);
218 } else {
219 return __ Uint32LessThanOrEqual(
220 __ Word32Sub(instance_type, first_instance_type),
221 last_instance_type - first_instance_type);
222 }
223 }
224
225 LocalIsolate* isolate_ = __ data() -> isolate()->AsLocalIsolate();
226 JSHeapBroker* broker_ = __ data() -> broker();
227 LocalFactory* factory_ = isolate_->factory();
228};
